9 An Act relating to charter schools; amending 62 O.S.
2021, Section 203, which relates to the apportionment
10 of monies to the General Revenue Fund; providing
exception to requirement for investment monies to
11 return to the General Revenue Fund; amending 70 O.S.
2021, Section 3-142, as last amended by Section 2,
12 Chapter 294, O.S.L. 2025 (70 O.S. Supp. 2025, Section
3-142), which relates to charter school funding;
13 removing reference to prohibition on issuing bonds;
clarifying repayment obligations for the state in
14 certain circumstances; stating legislative findings;
creating the Revolving Loan Fund Program for Charter
15 School Capital Expenditures; describing Revolving
Loan Fund Program management; providing Revolving
16 Loan Fund Program purpose; allowing a third-party
financial administrator to set interest rates on
17 loans to charter schools; stating loan recipients;
restricting loan usage for specific purposes;
18 providing loan eligibility; creating the Charter
School Loan Revolving Fund; providing fund purposes
19 and limitations; allowing appropriations; providing
procedure for approval and payment of funds; allowing
20 the promulgation of rules; creating the Charter
School Bond Credit Enhancement Program; prescribing
21 program eligibility; outlining program approval
process; mandating selection of third-party financial
22 administrator; requiring interception of State Aid
funds to pay bond obligations; providing permitted
23 reserve account uses; prohibiting revoking or
amending of payment directive; limiting payment
24 sources; creating the Charter School Bond Credit
